My Meme

As I scoured through the internet for meme formats, I came across one which I believed was not only funny, but also perfectly reflected how my emotions were as I was learning how to code in R, so I decided to find the individual images online and pair them with original captions that mirrored my reality.

library(magick)

#first panel
img <- image_blank(width = 275, height = 225, color = "white") %>%
  image_annotate("You have to make", color = "black", size = 25, 
                 location = "+30+70") %>%
  image_annotate("a meme using R", color = "black", size=25, gravity="center")

#second panel
panik <- image_read("https://i.etsystatic.com/20023820/r/il/e12dd6/2885404230/il_1588xN.2885404230_tb41.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(250)

#third panel
text_2 <- image_blank(width = 275, height = 225, color = "white") %>%
  image_annotate("You finally make", color = "black", size = 25, location="+40+70") %>%
  image_annotate("the meme", color = "black", size=25, gravity="center")

#fourth panel
kalm <- image_read("https://i.etsystatic.com/20023820/r/il/f37ede/2933086041/il_1588xN.2933086041_i98v.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(250)

#fifth panel
text_3 <- image_blank(width = 275, height = 225, color = "white") %>%
  image_annotate("Now you have", color = "black", size = 25, location="+55+70") %>%
  image_annotate("to make", color = "black", size=25, gravity="center") %>%
  image_annotate("a gif", color="black", size=25, location="+110+130")

#sixth panel
second_panik <- image_read("https://camo.githubusercontent.com/a02ebcf8141889a2ac8914df3517a93b53d68e350e6f12eb7cb9a37380d4289f/68747470733a2f2f692e696d6775722e636f6d2f426a4b5445386d2e6a706567") %>%
  image_scale("250")

first_row <- c(img, panik) %>%
  image_append()

second_row <- c(text_2, kalm) %>%
  image_append()

third_row <- c(text_3, second_panik) %>%
  image_append()

meme <- c(first_row, second_row, third_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

In all honesty, the idea for this animated gif came about from being hungry and thinking of donuts, so I thought why not make a gif which shows the full process of a donut being eaten, so I, once again, scoured the web for suitable images and annotated each frame with the text “nom” to describe the sound of the donut being eaten.

library(magick)

#all file images that are being initialized
first_frame <- image_read("donut1.jpeg") 
second_frame <- image_read("donut2.jpeg")
third_frame <- image_read("donut3.jpeg")
fourth_frame <- image_read("donut4.jpeg")
fifth_frame <- image_read("donut5.jpeg")

#first frame
frame1 <- first_frame %>%
  image_annotate("nom",size=40, color="black", location="+20+67") %>%
  image_scale(200) #resizing image so it doesn't take too much space

#second frame
frame2 <- second_frame %>%
  image_annotate("nom", size=80, color="black", gravity="north") %>%
  image_scale(200)

#third frame
frame3 <- third_frame %>%
  image_annotate("nom", size = 100, color="black", degrees=60, location="+400+100") %>%
  image_scale(200)

#fourth frame
frame4 <- fourth_frame %>%
  image_annotate("NOM", size=120, color="black",gravity="center") %>%
  image_scale(200)

#fifth frame
frame5 <- fifth_frame %>%
  image_annotate("*burp*", size=30, color="black", gravity="center") %>%
  image_scale(200)

#creating the 'gif' class
gif <- c(frame1,frame2,frame3,frame4,frame5)
image_animate(gif, fps=1)

#saving the gif as a '.gif' file 
image_write(gif, "my_animation.gif")
